title: Replace Webviews by Chrome Custom Tabs
message:
Replace Webviews by Chrome Custom Tabs

Using WebViews has advantages as it is a way to get native Webpage experience.
However, with it being somewhat coupled to the system, it might not be the
most secure/fast solution available.

Let's use the Chrome Tabs which are proven to be faster and be updated alongside
a user's compatible browser: (Mostly Chrome in that case)

- Add an Intent call to a web browser with an extra to a Custom tab if the said
device supports it.
- Remove BiblioFragment and MonETSFragment which aren't required anymore
- Replace "FRAGMENT" constants by "ITEM" as some items aren't technically
fragments anymore
- webservices.xml: Add the ETS library link as it was a constant initially.

title: TodayWidgetConfigureActivity: Remove unneeded return
message:
TodayWidgetConfigureActivity: Remove unneeded return

Like Android Studio says:

"Reports on any unneccessary return statements at the end of
constructors and methods returning void. These may safely be
removed".

title: TodayWidgetConfigureActivity: Add a default opacity constant
message:
TodayWidgetConfigureActivity: Add a default opacity constant

Easier to change it on the road after...

title: TodayWidgetConfigureActivity: Remove constant values in getSharedPreferences()
message:
TodayWidgetConfigureActivity: Remove constant values in getSharedPreferences()

It is recommended to use defined variables instead of constant
values because it might be possible that they change in possible
future revisions of Android. (Not that I believe that it will be
actually changed since SharedPreferences has been there for a bit)

In that case, let's do it for the good practices.

title: TodayWidgetConfigureActivity: Add default values
message:
TodayWidgetConfigureActivity: Add default values

If somebody previously configured a widget inside the application
and removes it afterward, he/she might want to reconfigure the
widget with the same attributes as before.

Since the preferences for a given widget are removed once it gets
deleted, add the required keys in order to save that said
preference.

message:
AndroidCalendarManager: Close dem cursors

Shaddap with those warnings!!

title: AndroidCalendarManager: Define OWNER_ACCOUNT
message:
AndroidCalendarManager: Define OWNER_ACCOUNT

As defined by the Android documentation,
OWNER_ACCOUNT must be defined when creating a
calendar. It was previously there but commented for
tests. More info on this available here:

https://developer.android.com/reference/android/provider/CalendarContract.Calendars.html

Let's place the owner account to the ETSMobile user. This
should fix some issues related to some calendar apps
crashing when trying to edit them (SPlanner on Samsung
devices for example)

title: HoraireFragment: Give the possibility to choose a schedule when exporting
message:
HoraireFragment: Give the possibility to choose a schedule when exporting

When exporting a schedule to a calendar all the given
schedules exposed get exported to the user's calendar
application. This might be an unwanted behavior
as the user might not want all of them. (For example, he/
she only wants the courses)

Give the choice to the user to select which calendar type
he/she wants.

At the same time, refactor the single AsyncTask for
HoraireManger as an inner class. nnerclass.

title: BottinDetailsFragment: Create phone link independant on region
message:
BottinDetailsFragment: Create phone link independant on region

Linkify when doing addLinks() is dependant on the device's
default locale in order to format correctly the given text.
Some devices might be configured in locales different from
North America. In such a case, the phone number won't
have it's appropriate link as described here:

http://stackoverflow.com/a/40946996

Only verify if the phone number "can" be valid and create a
link for it. (Since we can't really validate the phone number
as such but all the numbers in the Directory should be valid
in theory)

title: J'ai changé un peu le resize selon l'index (Thibaut a dit qu'on va regarder…
message: J'ai changé un peu le resize selon l'index (Thibaut a dit qu'on va regarder comment bien faire ça). Pour une raison quelqconque, mon datamanager avait une méthode dupliquer (??) donc j'ai effacer le duplicata.

title: La page des partenaires fonctionnent! Il y a maintenant une gridView, un resize…
message: La page des partenaires fonctionnent! Il y a maintenant une gridView, un resize selon l'index du sponsor et les sponsors sont stored dans une database (au cas où l'utilisateur n'a pas internet!). De plus, un click sur le partenaire amène l'utilisateur sur le site web du partenaire!

title: Thibaut m'a fait réaliser que mon app crashait si l'utilisateur n'avais pas de…
message: Thibaut m'a fait réaliser que mon app crashait si l'utilisateur n'avais pas de connection internet..... j'ai corrigé afin de garder le même comportement que le newsFragment, c'est-à-dire si on a pas internet, il y a page blanche...

title: I changed the way that our sponsors are displayed in the sponsor fragment.…
message: I changed the way that our sponsors are displayed in the sponsor fragment. Instead of being hard-coded, we now get them from the amazon test server dynamically. I also made it so the index changes the size of the sponsor.

title: Made a change in MoodleCoursesAdapter. When there was a big list of courses and…
message: Made a change in MoodleCoursesAdapter. When there was a big list of courses and the user scrolled down, the TextViews were disordered and got mixed up, misrepresenting the courses they should represent (for example, showing TIN502 when the course should be ELE430). This only happened when the user scrolled the listView. My change makes it so that the textViews never get disordered, even when the user scrolls around.

title: Fixed a bug where if the student changed his schedule, the "today" tab might not…
message: Fixed a bug where if the student changed his schedule, the "today" tab might not put the classes in an obvious chronological order.

title: Fixed the HTTPFragment crash, but there is still presence of the "infinite…
message: Fixed the HTTPFragment crash, but there is still presence of the "infinite loading" loop that I suspect has something to do with the SpiceRequest.
